<HEAD>Field Museum Will Give Merit Award To British Natural Historian</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sir David Attenborough, the British zoologist,
natural historian and filmmaker, is to receive the Award of Merit
from the Field Museum of Natural History's Founders' Council.
   The award is presented periodically to people who have made
significant contributions to the study of natural history. It will
be given to Attenborough tonight after the council's annual
meeting, the museum said.
   Attenborough is known for ``Life on Earth'' and ``The Living
Planet,'' two popular programs aired by the Public Broadcasting
System and British Broadcasting Co.
