<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Reiche     09-14 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Reiche,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>AP Berlin Correspondent Thomas Reiche Dies at 68</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomas Reiche, an editor in the West Berlin bureau
of The Associated Press for 25 years, has died at the age of 68.
   Reiche joined The AP in 1950 and became a member of the Berlin
staff six years later. Among the stories he covered was the
building of the Berlin Wall in August 1961.
   He was named to head the AP's German-language desk in West
Berlin in 1967 and retired in 1981.
   Reiche died of an intestinal tumor on Monday night, his family
said. Survivors include his wife, Waltraud Thiele-Reiche of West
Berlin and four children.
   Funeral services were scheduled for Friday at the Martin Luther
Cemetery in Tegel, West Berlin.
</TEXT>
