<HEAD>Man Charged in Actor's Death Pleads Guilty to Drunken Driving</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORRANCE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The man charged in the traffic accident
that killed ``Hill Street Blues'' actor Trinidad Silva Jr. has
pleaded guilty to drunken driving and vehicular manslaughter.
   Douglas Robert Owens, 35, was held on $25,000 bail for
sentencing Oct. 4. He pleaded guilty Tuesday, said Al Albergate,
spokesman for the district attorney's office.
   Owens apparently ran a stop light and collided with a pickup
truck driven by Silva on July 30, police said. Silva's wife Sofia,
28, and 2-year-old son were not seriously injured.
   Silva appeared as a gang member in the movie ``Colors,'' and as
the wiseacre gang leader Jesus Martinez on television's ``Hill
Street Blues.''
