<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Heroin-Sewer     09-14 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Heroin-Sewer,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Officers Dig Up Sewer To Find Heroin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DURHAM, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police officers not afraid of getting their
hands dirty excavated a sewer to find 40 packets of heroin flushed
down the toilet.
   ``One more flush and the heroin would have been gone,'' said
Capt. E.E. Sarvis of the police Organized Crime Division.
   Vice officers went after the drugs after drug raid at a house
early Tuesday.
   ``They apparently saw us coming and flushed it down the
toilet,'' Sarvis said. ``We dug up the sewer line. We knocked a
hole in it and right there we found a bundle with 20 bags of heroin
in it.''
   A second bundle of 20 bags was found farther down the line in
the backyard of the house, Sarvis said.
   Phillip Anthony Jones, 37, and Ernest Moore, 40, were charged
with drug offenses and released on $10,000 and $3,000 bail
respectively, police said.
