<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Britain-Mail     09-14 0105</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Mail,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mail to Great Britain Still Halted</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Postal Service on Wednesday urged
Americans to withhold mail to Great Britain, despite the settlement
of the mail workers strike in that country.
   Mail to Britain was embargoed last week because of the strike,
and U.S. officials said they would return Britain-bound items to
the senders.
   Although an agreement to settle the strike was reached Monday, a
huge backlog of mail remains to be sorted and delivered there, and
U.S. officials said it is expected to be at least a week before
they begin accepting mail addressed to the United Kingdom.
</TEXT>
