<HEAD>Thief Might Want To Read First</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SCRANTON, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The thief who took a car from a garage may
want to read the instructions next time.
   Police found the 1978 Volkswagen Rabbit, owned by Julie Acoe and
John Brennan, on Tuesday after it had crashed into a 10-foot chain
link fence.
   The owners told police the vehicle had been left earlier at Main
Auto Repair about four blocks from the accident scene.
   The keys were left under the seat and a note was left on the
steering wheel, warning garage workers not to drive the car because
of problems with the brakes, the owners reported.
   No one had been arrested as of Wednesday, Lt. Robert Scott said.
