<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>MASERU: gun fire.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The outcome of the shootout was not immediately known, but at
least eight ambulances were seen taking away dead or injured
people. About 70 people were aboard the bus, which was hijacked
Tuesday night.
   The shooting broke out about 20 minutes after the pope arrived
in Maseru, eight hours behind schedule. The hijackers earlier had
demanded to meet with the pope and Lesotho's king, Moshoeshoe II, a
government official said.
   The gunfire was heard at the site where the bus was parked, and
flares lit up the sky. Reporters were blocked from getting close
enough to determine what was happening but saw at least one nun
among the bloodied people taken away.
   Police ordered journalists at the scene to disperse and then
chased them away with whips.
