<HEAD>Stakes Are High in Celebrity Stake-outs</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Star Hounds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When Don Johnson and Barbra Streisand began
dating, photos of the two together could bring $25,000 in worldwide
sales, according to celebrity photographer Phil Ramey.
   Exclusives of Michael J. Fox and Tracy Pollan on their honeymoon
could fetch more than $20,000.
   Cher and boyfriend Rob Camilletti, on the other hand, are old
news these days: Pictures of the two are worth only about $100.
``Unless, of course, they got married,'' Ramey said. ``Then they'd
be worth $10,000 and up.''
   It's not just celebrity shots that produce profits. Ramey's
pictures of singer Michael Jackson's huge ranch near Santa Barbara
sold for more than $10,000, he said.
