<HEAD>Oregon Crop Sets Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oregon's strawberry harvest yielded a
record 101.4 million pounds of the sweet fruit this year, the
Oregon Agricultural Statistics Service said.
   The harvest, picked from 7,800 acres, is 8 percent larger than
last year's production of 93.6 million pounds, the service said in
a report released last week. The previous record crop was 100.1
million pounds harvested in 1964 from 13,900 acres.
   Oregon is the nation's second-largest strawberry producer after
California.
